<TITLE> Bail stayed of convict Pappu in Ahsanullah murder case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 20 (bdnews24.com)The Appellate Division on Monday stayed a bail order granted to Rakib Uddin Sarcar Pappu, who was given a life sentence for the murder of Awami League MP Ahsanullah Master in 2005. The High Court had earlier granted Pappu a six-month interim bail on appeal. Justice Mohammad Abdul Aziz stayed the bail order on a government appeal. In May 2004, assailants shot and killed Ahsanullah Master in Tongi, his brother Matiur Rahman filed a case with Tongi Police Station the following day. The high-profile case saw Pappu handed down a life sentence with six others in 2005, while twenty-two other accused in the case were given the death sentence. Two further suspects were acquitted in the trial. Additional attorney-general AKM Jahirul Haque stood for the government, Moudud Ahmed stood for Pappu in Monday's Appellate Division hearing. 
